OL,6,GThe reputation of any public service
OL,7,Gbroadcaster centres on its commitment
OL,8,Gto high quality news coverage.
OL,10,FNews is at the heart of the BBC and
OL,11,Fprovides the backbone of BBC One's
OL,12,Fschedule.
OL,14,FChannel 4 News is one of the legacies
OL,15,Fof the Channel 4 of old and might be
OL,16,Fsaid to be part of the soul and
OL,17,Fconscience of the channel.
OL,19,FIt was often highlighted by opponents
OL,20,Fof privatisation as a programme which
OL,21,Fcould have been put at risk.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G1/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35202
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1674627992
OL,6,FBut yet again ITV 1's scheduling of
OL,7,FNews at Ten is undermining what should
OL,8,Fbe one of the channel's flagships.
OL,10,FNews at Ten was brought back in 2008 `
OL,11,Finitially from Mondays to Thursdays but
OL,12,Fsoon afterwards the programme started
OL,13,Fto appear on Fridays too.
OL,15,FThe move was instigated by Michael
OL,16,FGrade who was well aware of the damage
OL,17,Fthe initial decision to axe News at Ten
OL,18,Fin 1999 had done.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G2/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35203
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1674627992
OL,6,FThe revival never regained the
OL,7,Faudiences of old ` and there is an
OL,8,Fargument that it isn't helpful to have
OL,9,Fthe news on both major channels
OL,10,Fsimultaneously ` but it was broadly
OL,11,Fwelcomed by journalists and others who
OL,12,Frealise the vital role high quality
OL,13,Fbroadcast journalism plays in a
OL,14,Fdemocratic society.
OL,16,FThe scheduling was never fixed and ITV
OL,17,Fappeared to toy with ditching the
OL,18,Fprogramme in 2017 when it experimented
OL,19,Fwith nightly chat shows at 10pm.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G3/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35204
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1674627992
OL,6,FBut in recent months there have been
OL,7,Fmore occasions when News at When has
OL,8,Freturned. There has scarcely been a
OL,9,Fweek for some time when the programme
OL,10,Fhas been shown at 10pm each night.
OL,12,FSometimes this has been because of
OL,13,Ffootball ` though it should be noted
OL,14,Fthat the BBC usually manages to get to
OL,15,Fthe news on time unless the game goes
OL,16,Fto extra time.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G4/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35205
SC,0005
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1674627992
OL,6,FSometimes though this is because the
OL,7,F9pm programme is longer than usual. A
OL,8,Fdeliberate decision was taken to
OL,9,Fcommission or schedule a programme
OL,10,Fwhich wasn't made for a 60-minute slot.
OL,12,FIn exceptional circumstances this is
OL,13,Fnot a problem but it seems to be
OL,14,Fbecoming commonplace.
OL,16,FFriday night saw a good example of
OL,17,Fthis.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G5/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35206
SC,0006
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1674627992
OL,6,FA repeat of Midsomer Murders pushed
OL,7,FNews at Ten back to 10.50pm. The same
OL,8,Fthing will happen this Friday. As far
OL,9,Fas I can recall, it was the first time
OL,10,Fsince 2004 when a routine scheduling
OL,11,Fdecision pushed the news past 10.30pm.
OL,13,FNeedless to say, the move seemed to
OL,14,Fboost the audience for the BBC News.
OL,16,FThere would seem to be little
OL,17,Fcommercial advantage in the move as ITV
OL,18,F1 currently runs few ads between 10pm
OL,19,Fand 11pm. The last breaks during
OL,20,FMidsomer Murders were filled by
OL,21,Fpromotions.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G6/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35207
SC,0007
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1674627992
OL,6,FYet it also meant excellent journalism
OL,7,F` including a powerful piece on an
OL,8,Fupsurge of serous Covid cases in China
OL,9,F` was seen by a relatively modest
OL,10,Faudience.
OL,12,FIt really is time for this scheduling
OL,13,Fshenanigans to end.
OL,15,FWould ITV 1 be better off anchoring the
OL,16,Fbulletin at 10.30pm? That way those who
OL,17,Fwanted to could easily watch the
OL,18,Fflagship bulletins of both main
OL,19,Fchannels?
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G7/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,35208
SC,0008
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F352A1674627992
OL,6,FMight it even be acceptable to move the
OL,7,Fprogramme to 11pm given that ITV now
OL,8,Fshows an hour of national news in the
OL,9,Fearly evening? (Even it is cut back to
OL,10,F30 minutes not infrequently.)
OL,12,FWhat might happen if ITV 1 gets
OL,13,Fpermission to run more ads in peak time
OL,14,Fwith a full 12 minutes allocated to the
OL,15,F10pm hour? If ITV cannot commit to
OL,16,Fgiving News at Ten a fixed berth, it is
OL,17,Fbetter to move it out of peak rather
OL,18,Fthen see it move like a ship in a
OL,19,Fstorm.
OL,3,CAre we slowly drifting from News at Ten
OL,4,Cto News at When again?
